<p>We’ve been in a death march of <a href="https://docs.google.com/a/fedarch.org/document/d/1cGkTaeY2dfvAV6Za97OGe8zNLvF_YMyPX7qiVEFNC8o/edit#">requirements</a> generation.</p>

<p><a href="http://www.fedarch.org/wordpress/?attachment_id=338"><img src="http://www.fedarch.org/wordpress/wp-content/uploads//2012/09/WS4135_clean-300x225.jpg" alt="" /></a></p>

<p>Right now we’re engaged in a series of day long meetings exploring the requirements of our software. Schedule sliip is fun, but I think this is helping everyone develop the same locally true language (Galison) and a shared mental-model of everything that this incredibly… complex program is supposed to do.</p>

<p>Wheee!</p>
